%% Diagram: Two-Phase Commit happy path and the blocking failure mode
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Coordinator
    participant P1 as Participant 1
    participant P2 as Participant 2

    rect rgb(232, 244, 253)
    note over C,P2: Phase 1 — Prepare (voting)
    C->>P1: PREPARE
    C->>P2: PREPARE
    P1->>P1: write redo/undo,\nacquire locks
    P2->>P2: write redo/undo,\nacquire locks
    P1-->>C: VOTE-YES
    P2-->>C: VOTE-YES
    end

    rect rgb(220, 240, 220)
    note over C,P2: Phase 2 — Commit (decision)
    C->>C: write COMMIT to log
    C->>P1: COMMIT
    C->>P2: COMMIT
    P1->>P1: commit, release locks
    P2->>P2: commit, release locks
    P1-->>C: ACK
    P2-->>C: ACK
    end

    rect rgb(255, 232, 232)
    note over C,P2: Failure mode — coordinator crash after PREPARE
    C-xC: crash
    note over P1,P2: P1 and P2 voted YES, hold locks,\ncannot commit (no decision),\ncannot abort (might have committed).\nThey block until coordinator recovers.
    end
